description: The statue had become a landmark for hikers in Bavaria, but no-one really knew how it came to be there.

maintext: One theory, reported by German media, is that the sculpture was an unwanted birthday gift, carved by a group of young men as a practical joke for a friend. When the present was rejected, they pulled it up the mountain on a sledge, leaving it for others to appreciate.
